// Pokemon Insurgence curated patches.
//
// Source-text fixes for known Insurgence bugs that cripple iOS play.
// Replaces the runtime postload override approach with a script-source
// rewrite that's authoritative and platform-portable.
//
// Format: JoiPlay-compatible. Keys without prefix do literal substring
// replace; keys prefixed with "[regex]" use std::regex_replace
// ECMAScript syntax.
{
  "rpgm": [
    // 1. Fix `getRegion` Ruby-1.8 idiom that crashes on Ruby 3,
    //    AND make it locale-aware off Windows.
    //
    // Original (Scripts/186-Deuks_Region.rb:16-31):
    //   def getRegion
    //     z = getCountryCode.to_i
    //     z=1 if (z==2)
    //     x = z.to_s.split('').map      # bare .map returns
    //                                   # Enumerator on Ruby 3
    //     y = x[0]                      # Enumerator has no #[]
    //     m = y.to_i
    //     ...
    //   end
    //
    // The function feeds into 157-PokemonUtilities.rb's language
    // dispatch. The original derives a language id from the first
    // digit of `getCountryCode` (a Win32 Geo ID read from the
    // registry: 244 = USA, 81 = Japan, 84 = France, etc.). On
    // iOS there's no registry, so `getCountryCode` always returns
    // 0 - effectively "Unknown" - and Insurgence's UI silently
    // falls back to English regardless of user locale.
    //
    // Replacement: branch on `System.user_language[0..1]` (the
    // ISO 639-1 language code from `NSLocale.languageCode` /
    // `mkxp_sys::getSystemLanguage()`) and return PE's canonical
    // pbGetLanguage values. The map matches the upstream PE 21
    // implementation (Maruno17/pokemon-essentials, Data/Scripts/
    // 019_Utilities/001_Utilities.rb#pbGetLanguage):
    //
    //   ja -> 1 (Japanese)
    //   en -> 2 (English, also default)
    //   fr -> 3 (French)
    //   it -> 4 (Italian)
    //   de -> 5 (German)
    //   es -> 7 (Spanish)
    //   ko -> 8 (Korean)
    //
    // The `rescue "en"` guards against the `System` binding not
    // existing on bizarre setups (none expected on our iOS build,
    // belt-and-braces). `to_s[0..1]` handles both "en" and any
    // hypothetical full identifier ("en_US") even though our
    // engine returns the bare language code.
    //
    // Regex anchoring: lazy [\s\S]*? matches across newlines
    // (std::regex's `.` doesn't include newline). The closing
    // `end` must be at column 0 so the regex doesn't snap to an
    // inner if/elsif/end inside the original method body and
    // leave the outer end dangling (which would be a SyntaxError
    // and skip the whole script, surfacing as `NoMethodError:
    // undefined ... getRegion` from PokeBattle_Trainer).
    {
      "key": "[regex]def getRegion\\b[\\s\\S]*?\\nend\\b",
      "value": "def getRegion\n  lang = (System.user_language rescue \"en\").to_s\n  case lang[0..1]\n  when \"ja\" then return 1\n  when \"en\" then return 2\n  when \"fr\" then return 3\n  when \"it\" then return 4\n  when \"de\" then return 5\n  when \"es\" then return 7\n  when \"ko\" then return 8\n  end\n  return 2\nend"
    }
  ]
}
